<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Whirlpool washer jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Two representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Whirlpool washer service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool WTW8500DW Cabrio top-load, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Washer fills and agitates normally but stalls before spin cycle. F26 error code displayed at end of cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly failure, most common Cabrio service call (year 4-6 typical). Switch ohms-out reading inconsistent on bench test, contact intermittent. Drive system tested fine; drain pump tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly replacement with OEM Whirlpool part (in stock on the truck). Verified normal lid-lock engagement and full cycle progression including spin on test wash. F26 cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 50 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool WFW9620HC Duet front-load, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> F11 error code on every cycle. Washer wouldn't proceed past the wash phase. Owner reported a recent power flicker during a windstorm.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> F11 indicates a serial communication error between the CCU (main control board) and MCU (motor control unit). Harness inspection between the two boards confirmed solid connections. Diagnostic continuity testing confirmed the MCU was the failing component, incoming signal from CCU OK, outgoing motor command absent on multiple test cycles. Likely surge damage from the recent power event.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> MCU replacement with OEM Whirlpool part (1-day lead from authorized distribution; return visit). Verified normal F11-clear startup, full cycle test wash, motor control on all spin speeds.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $485 total. Two-visit repair (diagnostic + part install). Total time on-site across both visits: 1 hour 50 minutes.</p>
      </div>
